quran[23]{c,v,t}:
  26,184,Be wary of Him who created you and the earlier generations.’
  26,185,"They said, ‘Indeed you are one of the bewitched"
  26,186,"You are just a human being like us, and we indeed consider you to be a liar"
  26,187,"Make a fragment of the sky falls upon us, should you be truthful.’"
  26,188,"He said, ‘My Lord knows best what you are doing.’"
  26,189,"So they impugned him, and then they were overtaken by the punishment of the day of the overshadowing cloud. It was indeed the punishment of a terrible day"
  26,190,There is indeed a sign in that; but most of them do not have faith
  26,191,"Indeed your Lord is the All-mighty, the All-merciful"
  26,192,"This is indeed [a Book] sent down by the Lord of all the worlds"
  26,193,brought down by the Trustworthy Spirit
  26,194,upon your heart (so that you may be one of the warners)
  26,195,in a clear Arabic language
  26,196,"It is indeed [foretold] in the scriptures of the ancients"
  26,197,Is it not a sign for them that the learned of the Children of Israel recognize it
  26,198,Had We sent it down upon some non-Arab
  26,199,"and had he recited it to them, they would not have believed in it"
  26,200,This is how We let it pass through the hearts of the guilty
  26,201,they do not believe in it until they sight the painful punishment
  26,202,It will overtake them suddenly while they are unaware
  26,203,"Thereupon they will say, ‘Shall we be granted any respite?’"
  26,204,So do they seek to hasten on Our punishment
  26,205,"Tell me, should We let them enjoy for some years"
  26,206,then there comes to them what they have been promised